SIMPLE: whereof
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whereof
<hw>Where*of"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of which; of whom; formerly, also, with which; --
used relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do not find the certain numbers <qex>whereof</qex> their armies
did consist.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J. Davies.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let it work like Borgias' wine,⟦br⟧
<qex>Whereof</qex> his sire, the pope, was poisoned.</q>
<rj><qau>Marlowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Edward's seven sons, <qex>whereof</qex> thyself art one.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of what; -- used interrogatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whereof</qex> was the house built?</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whereon</ent>⟦br⟧
